# =============================================================================
# Vibe app — copy to `.env` at repo root. Never commit `.env`.
# Production: inject the same variable names via the host (12-factor).
#
# Quiets dotenv’s default “◇ injected env …” log (optional; app also uses quiet: true).
# =============================================================================
DOTENV_CONFIG_QUIET=true
#
# PowerVibe apps: in dev the browser calls Koa at `http://<same-host>:VITE_FLIGHT_PORT/api/powervibe/apps` (and per-app `.../apps/:appId`).
# (default port 3000). Set `VITE_FLIGHT_PORT` to the same value as `FLIGHT_PORT`. Optional: `VITE_KOA_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:3000`.
# VITE_FLIGHT_PORT=3000
# Per-app preview iframe (Flight prod + vite build on port 4000). Override if tunneling or binding elsewhere.
# VITE_POWERVIBE_BUNDLE_PREVIEW_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:4000
# PowerVibe header: Tutorial (Slidev). Omit to use http://localhost:3030/ (Slidev dev binds localhost by default).
# Root URL opens slide 2; set a path to start elsewhere (e.g. …/1, …/presenter) if needed.
# VITE_POWERVIBE_GUIDE_SLIDEV_URL=http://localhost:3030/
# PowerVibe AI: SSE streaming + progress (Thinking… → char count). Requires backend restart after changing.
# VITE_POWERVIBE_CHAT_STREAM=1
#
# Dev stack: `npm run start:docker` then `npm run start:app` (Flight + embedded Vite).
# Open the app at http://localhost:3001 — Redis must be reachable (see compose.yml).
#
#   Required for Gemini plan chat (Plan.backend.ts):
#     GEMINI_API_KEY
#
#   Flight / Redis (required for Flight):
#     FLIGHT_REDIS_HOST, FLIGHT_REDIS_PORT
#     FLIGHT_MAX_WORKERS — optional; Node cluster **HTTP worker** count for platform Flight (defaults to CPU count).
#       Embedded dev Vite binds **3001 once** (lead worker); does not require setting this to 1.
#       Per-app bundle Flight spawned by PowerVibe forces FLIGHT_MAX_WORKERS=1 separately (see powervibeBundleRunner).
#
#   Optional:
#     FLIGHT_QUIET_HTTP=1    → disable `koa-logger` per-request lines on **platform** Flight (bundle Flight sets this via powervibeBundleRunner).
#     FLIGHT_PORT            → Koa API port (default 3000). Vite dev proxy `/api` → this port only (never 3001).
#     VITE_KOA_PORT          → optional override for that proxy if Koa is not on FLIGHT_PORT.
#     FLIGHT_EXCLUDE_PATHS   → optional comma-separated dirs under app_home excluded from `*.backend.ts` discovery (merged with `--exclude_paths`; PowerVibe start script passes `bundles` on the CLI).
#     FLIGHT_PAYLOAD_LIMIT   → Koa `koa-bodyparser` JSON limit (default `1mb`). Raise for large PowerVibe `App.vue` saves, e.g. `64mb`.
#                              Mic transcription POSTs base64 JSON; long recordings exceed `1mb` quickly — use e.g. `16mb` or `64mb`.
#     GEMINI_MODEL          → optional; stronger models often help long PowerVibe `App.vue` / data-story turns (trade cost vs quality). Pasted “master prompts”: docs/powervibe-master-prompt-dialect.md
#
# PowerVibe `App.vue` max UTF-8 size on PUT (Powervibe.backend.ts): default **50 MiB** in code; override with bytes, max **200 MiB**:
# POWERVIBE_APP_SOURCE_MAX_BYTES=52428800
#
# --- VITE_PLAN_API_URL (browser → plan API) ---
# Flight dev: UI on http://localhost:3001, Koa on FLIGHT_PORT (default 3000).
#   RECOMMENDED: leave VITE_PLAN_API_URL unset → fetch("/api/plan") → Vite proxies to Koa.
#   WRONG: VITE_PLAN_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3001 → request goes to Vite as .../plan (no /api)
#          → 404 "Not Found"; Gemini is never called.
#   OK (absolute to Koa): VITE_PLAN_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000
#   OK (via Vite proxy): VITE_PLAN_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3001/api  → .../api/plan hits proxy
#
#   Not read by Plan.backend.ts yet (reserved / future Vertex):
#     GOOGLE_CLOUD_* , GOOGLE_CLIENT_EMAIL , GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY ,
#     GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS
#
# =============================================================================

FLIGHT_PORT=3000
# Session max age in ms (Flight reads FLIGHT_SESSION_DURATION_MS; if missing/invalid you get a console warning).
FLIGHT_SESSION_DURATION_MS=86400000
FLIGHT_REDIS_HOST=127.0.0.1
FLIGHT_REDIS_PORT=6379
# FLIGHT_MAX_WORKERS=4
# Allow large PowerVibe `PUT …/apps/:id` bodies (Flight `koa-bodyparser`; default is often `1mb`):
# FLIGHT_PAYLOAD_LIMIT=64mb
# Optional cap override (bytes); code default is 50 MiB, max 200 MiB:
# POWERVIBE_APP_SOURCE_MAX_BYTES=52428800
# Max characters of `App.vue` injected into PowerVibe AI system context per turn (default 80000):
# POWERVIBE_IDEATION_SOURCE_CONTEXT_CHARS=80000
# Max Scribe chat rows sent to Gemini per turn (tail of thread; default 100, max 500):
# POWERVIBE_CHAT_GEMINI_MAX_MESSAGES=100
# Strip ```vue from older assistant rows in Gemini input only (default on). Set false to keep full history in the model tail:
# POWERVIBE_CHAT_OMIT_HISTORICAL_VUE_FENCES=false
# Cap for workspace package.json dependency list in PowerVibe system prompt (default 6000):
# POWERVIBE_IDEATION_DEPS_SUMMARY_MAX_CHARS=6000

# Deprecated: do not use for Vite proxy (removed). Set FLIGHT_PORT (or VITE_KOA_PORT) only.
# PLAN_API_PORT=3000

# VITE_PLAN_API_URL=
# VITE_PLAN_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000
# VITE_PLAN_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3001/api

# --- Gemini (AI Studio) ---
# Key from https://aistudio.google.com/apikey (Generative Language API must be enabled on the project).
# From https://aistudio.google.com/apikey — value usually starts with AIza… (not AQ.* OAuth-style tokens).
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# Default in code matches this: newer Flash preview. If your key returns 404, use a stable id from
# https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models — e.g. gemini-2.5-flash / gemini-2.5-pro, or Gemini 3 family:
#   gemini-3-flash-preview (default in code), gemini-3.1-pro-preview (stronger / higher cost).
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-3-flash-preview
# Mic transcription defaults to gemini-2.5-flash in code (gemini-2.0-flash unavailable for new keys). Optional override:
# GEMINI_TRANSCRIBE_MODEL=gemini-3-flash-preview

# --- Postgres (compose `postgres` service; used by Scribe) ---
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://vibe:vibe@127.0.0.1:5432/vibe

# --- Scribe (PowerVibe multi-app persistence) ---
# Local dev: optional — when unset, Flight uses http://127.0.0.1:1337 (same as host Scribe after `npm run start:docker`).
# Production: set SCRIBE_URL explicitly (e.g. http://scribe:1337 when Flight runs in Compose).
# SCRIBE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:1337
# If Flight runs inside Compose on the same network as `scribe`, use: SCRIBE_URL=http://scribe:1337
# The `scribe` container receives DB/Redis via compose (see compose.yml); no need to duplicate SCRIBE_APP_* on the host unless you run the Scribe CLI locally.

# --- GCP / Vertex (not used by Plan.backend.ts yet) ---
GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=
GOOGLE_CLOUD_LOCATION=global
GOOGLE_CLOUD_EMBEDDING_LOCATION=us-central1
GOOGLE_CLIENT_EMAIL=
GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY=
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=

# PostgreSQL (used by Scribe)
SCRIBE_APP_DB_HOST=postgres
SCRIBE_APP_DB_USER=postgres
SCRIBE_APP_DB_PASS=postgres
SCRIBE_APP_DB_NAME=sp10alpha
SCRIBE_APP_MODE=development